cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language generation and sentiment analysis. The use of self-attentive recursive autoencoders and personalized decoders also suggests a focus on language modeling and text generation. Additionally, the paper may also fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) due to the use of deep learning techniques and the development of a novel model. The inclusion of human evaluations and statistical linguistics analysis may also suggest a connection to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
